HEADWORD: old-womanish
<hw>old`-wom`an*ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like an old
woman; anile; primly fastidious; old-maidish.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Old`-wom"an*ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fussy, old-maidish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

